1
00:00:13,967 --> 00:00:15,867
<i> Hazel.</i>

2
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,433
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

3
00:00:17,567 --> 00:00:20,700
<i>I'm just wishing her good luck
with her operation tomorrow.</i>

4
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:22,800
<i>Didn't I tell you to stay away
from Felma?</i>

5
00:00:22,933 --> 00:00:24,133
<i>- Bye, friend!
- Leave!</i>

6
00:00:24,267 --> 00:00:26,067
<i>They can't just take me out
of the picture.</i>

7
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:27,700
<i> After the surgery,</i>

8
00:00:27,833 --> 00:00:30,733
<i>I will try to poison her mind
again.</i>

9
00:00:30,867 --> 00:00:32,967
<i> What if my memories disappear?</i>

10
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:35,233
<i> What if I don't recognize you?</i>

11
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:38,767
<i> I'm scared.</i>

12
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:40,900
<i> Felma's operation scares me.</i>

13
00:00:41,033 --> 00:00:44,367
<i>What if something bad happens
to Felma?</i>

14
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:47,100
<i>I won't be able to handle that,
bro.</i>

15
00:00:47,233 --> 00:00:48,500
<i>Mom, we should still see
that smile</i>

16
00:00:48,633 --> 00:00:49,767
<i> after your operation, okay?</i>

17
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:51,700
<i>Doctor, please take care of her.</i>

18
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:53,400
<i> I can't promise,</i>

19
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:57,467
<i>but I will try my best
to remember all of you</i>

20
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,033
<i> when I come out of here.</i>

21
00:01:00,533 --> 00:01:03,567
<i>Doc, how was it?
Is the surgery over?</i>

22
00:01:03,700 --> 00:01:05,300
<i> We had a successful operation.</i>

23
00:01:08,700 --> 00:01:10,333
<i> Thank God!</i>

24
00:01:10,467 --> 00:01:11,700
<i> No!</i>

25
00:01:11,833 --> 00:01:13,100
<i> No!</i>

26
00:01:13,233 --> 00:01:14,767
<i> No, no!</i>

27
00:01:14,900 --> 00:01:16,100
<i> No!</i>

28
00:01:16,233 --> 00:01:17,700
<i> So you're disappointed?</i>

29
00:01:17,833 --> 00:01:20,900
<i>You're in a bad mood because
Felma survived the surgery?</i>

30
00:01:22,133 --> 00:01:23,033
Obviously.

31
00:01:23,967 --> 00:01:25,200
What else do you think?

32
00:01:25,333 --> 00:01:26,433
<i> Hazel,</i>

33
00:01:26,567 --> 00:01:28,300
<i> I told you.</i>

34
00:01:28,433 --> 00:01:30,733
<i>You can't just wish death
on anyone.</i>

35
00:01:31,900 --> 00:01:34,133
Felma isn't just anyone.

36
00:01:35,733 --> 00:01:37,467
She's ruining my life.

37
00:01:39,033 --> 00:01:40,733
If I weren't afraid of God,

38
00:01:41,933 --> 00:01:44,333
I wouldn't just wish
she were dead.

39
00:01:45,967 --> 00:01:47,433
I'd do it myself.

40
00:01:48,567 --> 00:01:50,767
<i>I'm telling you, if you do that,</i>

41
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:52,767
<i> I'll be out of your life.</i>

42
00:01:52,900 --> 00:01:54,867
Of course, I won't.

43
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:58,133
Just keep me updated, okay?

44
00:01:59,833 --> 00:02:03,333
Find out when I can visit Felma.
Like when no one's watching.

45
00:02:03,967 --> 00:02:04,533
<i> No!</i>

46
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:06,133
Alice,

47
00:02:06,967 --> 00:02:08,067
please.

48
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:09,967
Fine, I'll try. But...

49
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,067
Thank you.

50
00:02:37,467 --> 00:02:38,433
Nurse.

51
00:02:40,700 --> 00:02:41,700
Nurse!

52
00:02:45,167 --> 00:02:46,167
Nurse!

53
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:48,967
Nurse, the patient is awake.

54
00:02:51,833 --> 00:02:52,867
Nurse!

55
00:02:53,667 --> 00:02:55,033
The patient's awake now.

56
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:08,000
Dad, come again?

57
00:03:08,133 --> 00:03:11,433
I told you, we shouldn't have
come home yet.

58
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:12,433
See?

59
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:14,067
We weren't there
when Mom woke up.

60
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:15,733
Wait, Coleen.
We can't hear Dad. Dad.

61
00:03:15,867 --> 00:03:17,533
Yeah. I can't understand
what Dad says.

62
00:03:17,667 --> 00:03:21,267
Dad? Hello? What is it again?

63
00:03:21,433 --> 00:03:27,267
I was saying your mom seemed out
of it when she woke up earlier.

64
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:29,467
She was kind of spaced out.

65
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:33,033
But Mom's okay, right, Dad?

66
00:03:33,167 --> 00:03:36,533
The doctor said it was fine.

67
00:03:36,667 --> 00:03:38,400
Her brain is just swelling
right now.

68
00:03:38,533 --> 00:03:40,533
But they've already given her
medication.

69
00:03:40,667 --> 00:03:44,133
But you said Mom was stuttering?

70
00:03:44,267 --> 00:03:46,100
They said it was normal.

71
00:03:46,233 --> 00:03:47,867
She only needs therapy.

72
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,667
But Dad, what did Mom tell you?

73
00:03:54,433 --> 00:03:55,533
Nothing.

74
00:03:55,667 --> 00:03:58,733
<i>Felma, I told you nothing bad
would happen.</i>

75
00:03:58,867 --> 00:03:59,933
<i> Love.</i>

76
00:04:04,333 --> 00:04:06,300
<i> Noah.</i>

77
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:15,033
But she kept saying your names.

78
00:04:15,167 --> 00:04:16,833
Sir Manuel, are you crying?

79
00:04:16,967 --> 00:04:18,067
What?

80
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:22,700
Yes, because...

81
00:04:23,267 --> 00:04:32,500
Didang, I'm just happy because
I was here when Felma woke up.

82
00:04:34,167 --> 00:04:35,733
- Dad.
- So sweet.

83
00:04:36,667 --> 00:04:40,133
I have to go now.
I'll call again later.

84
00:04:40,267 --> 00:04:41,233
Okay.

85
00:04:41,367 --> 00:04:42,900
- Be safe, Dad.
- Bye, Dad.

86
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:44,133
Wait, Sir.

87
00:04:44,267 --> 00:04:48,300
Did she only mention the kids?
Didn't she look for me?

88
00:04:48,433 --> 00:04:49,500
<i> Sir Manuel?</i>

89
00:04:51,533 --> 00:04:52,500
No.

90
00:04:53,567 --> 00:04:55,667
Sir Manuel's so grumpy.

91
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:56,967
He's mad.

92
00:04:57,100 --> 00:04:58,233
He's mad.

93
00:05:03,967 --> 00:05:05,567
Felma, don't forget me.

94
00:05:07,367 --> 00:05:09,100
I won't be able to handle it.

95
00:05:28,833 --> 00:05:29,867
Manuel.

96
00:05:31,767 --> 00:05:32,733
Manuel,

97
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,133
you're already tired.

98
00:05:35,733 --> 00:05:36,733
Scared.

99
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,333
Maybe you should get some rest.

100
00:05:41,733 --> 00:05:45,467
Don't worry about Felma.
She's now safe.

101
00:05:55,667 --> 00:05:56,667
I don't need that.

102
00:05:58,133 --> 00:05:59,133
Come on, Manuel.

103
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:00,933
Look at yourself.

104
00:06:01,067 --> 00:06:03,033
I said I don't need that!

105
00:06:04,333 --> 00:06:06,200
I was just trying to help.

106
00:06:09,567 --> 00:06:11,700
Manuel, I only wanted
to comfort you.

107
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:15,967
I remember when we were
in the ICU.

108
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:17,167
When...

109
00:06:18,267 --> 00:06:19,767
Jessica was there.

110
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:22,633
I also felt what you're feeling
right now.

111
00:06:23,867 --> 00:06:25,700
That's why I want to comfort you

112
00:06:25,833 --> 00:06:28,533
because you need someone
to encourage you.

113
00:06:28,667 --> 00:06:30,467
Stop bringing up Jessica.

114
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:35,267
My daughter has long been gone.

115
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,633
Stop.

116
00:06:37,767 --> 00:06:39,133
Leave.

117
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,733
What?

118
00:06:41,867 --> 00:06:44,067
Are you leaving or am I calling
the guard?

119
00:06:45,767 --> 00:06:47,600
I don't get it, Manuel.

120
00:06:50,167 --> 00:06:55,033
Is that easy for you
to embarrass me?

121
00:06:55,167 --> 00:06:56,433
To disrespect me?

122
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:58,700
Is that so easy for you?

123
00:07:01,533 --> 00:07:03,167
Hazel, you won't get
embarrassed...

124
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:04,333
You won't get disrespected...

125
00:07:04,467 --> 00:07:06,367
If you stay away from us.

126
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:07,933
Are you going to leave or not?

127
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:14,300
If I were you, Hazel,
I'd leave.

128
00:07:18,033 --> 00:07:19,533
I've talked to the hospital.

129
00:07:20,467 --> 00:07:23,600
I've already told them
to deny you entry.

130
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:27,100
The guards are on their way
here, too.

131
00:07:27,233 --> 00:07:33,200
So, if I were you, I'd leave
before I get dragged out.

132
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:37,300
Are you ganging up on me?

133
00:07:38,667 --> 00:07:40,067
What's this?

134
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:42,000
You just teamed up?

135
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:45,733
From rivals to what?

136
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,667
Brothers?

137
00:07:48,867 --> 00:07:50,133
What do you want me to do?

138
00:07:50,933 --> 00:07:54,367
Fight Noah like what you did
to Felma?

139
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:55,600
Is that what you want?

140
00:07:55,733 --> 00:07:56,467
No.

141
00:07:57,633 --> 00:07:59,500
But this close, Manuel?

142
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,200
What's this? Bromance?

143
00:08:03,033 --> 00:08:04,033
Since when?

144
00:08:05,133 --> 00:08:05,767
Why?

145
00:08:06,667 --> 00:08:07,733
What happened?

146
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:11,533
We don't owe you
any explanation, Hazel.

147
00:08:11,667 --> 00:08:13,900
Hazel, this doesn't involve you.
You're not part of this.

148
00:08:15,667 --> 00:08:17,033
You're so unfair.

149
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:21,800
Noah, who is your rival,
can stay here.

150
00:08:21,967 --> 00:08:23,067
He can stick his nose in.

151
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:24,833
But me...

152
00:08:24,967 --> 00:08:26,733
Felma and I are also rivals.

153
00:08:26,867 --> 00:08:28,867
And I'm your wife.

154
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,967
I want to comfort you.
That's why I'm here.

155
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:35,133
Felma was never your rival.

156
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,600
Felma is the only woman I love.

157
00:08:39,733 --> 00:08:41,000
Always has been.

158
00:08:41,133 --> 00:08:43,000
Still is.

159
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:44,333
No one else.

160
00:09:01,100 --> 00:09:04,333
Coleen, what did you wish for
on the falling star this time?

161
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:07,067
Sis, no.

162
00:09:07,633 --> 00:09:11,233
I only thanked God
because Mom's awake now.

163
00:09:13,167 --> 00:09:16,100
Can we go to the hospital?

164
00:09:16,967 --> 00:09:19,133
I want to see Mom badly.

165
00:09:19,867 --> 00:09:21,933
Me, too.

166
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:24,167
Let's go tomorrow.

167
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,200
The visiting hours are over.

168
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:29,933
We're family, not visitors.

169
00:09:30,833 --> 00:09:32,533
Sis, please?

170
00:09:32,967 --> 00:09:34,933
I'll call Jeff.
Let's ask her to drive for us.

171
00:09:35,067 --> 00:09:36,033
Sweetie, don't be stubborn.

172
00:09:36,767 --> 00:09:38,400
We'll go tomorrow.

173
00:09:38,533 --> 00:09:42,333
I only want to make sure
Mom's doing okay.

174
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:49,533
Didn't Dad say Mom's doing okay?

175
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:54,767
Let's trust in him. Why?
Don't you trust Dad?

176
00:09:55,967 --> 00:09:59,167
Why would he say Mom's okay
if she's not?

177
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,267
Don't worry.

178
00:10:01,433 --> 00:10:04,333
Dad won't leave Mom.

179
00:10:04,467 --> 00:10:06,600
He's totally watching over her,
right?

180
00:10:08,967 --> 00:10:13,167
Dad will update us if there are
improvements on Mom's condition.

181
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:16,100
Let's just wait. Okay?

182
00:10:19,133 --> 00:10:20,900
I can't take it, Alice.

183
00:10:22,233 --> 00:10:23,333
What happened?

184
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:27,867
Manuel and Noah ganged up on me.

185
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,067
Can you believe it?

186
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:33,667
Those who used to be rivals
have teamed up against me.

187
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:35,633
What did you do this time?

188
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,400
I just tried to comfort Manuel.

189
00:10:37,533 --> 00:10:39,067
You're so stubborn, friend.

190
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:43,500
Your husband's pushing you away,
and you just won't quit.

191
00:10:43,633 --> 00:10:45,000
I can't stop.

192
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:48,533
If I let my guard down
even for a second,

193
00:10:48,667 --> 00:10:50,300
I might be out of Manuel's life
for good.

194
00:10:50,433 --> 00:10:52,033
I can't...

195
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:55,633
Hello?

196
00:10:55,767 --> 00:10:56,800
Hello!

197
00:11:03,767 --> 00:11:04,667
Wait!

198
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:05,833
Wait!

199
00:11:11,967 --> 00:11:13,967
Noah, thank you for coming back.

200
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:18,400
Actually, I'm supposed to be
at the airport right now.

201
00:11:18,533 --> 00:11:20,733
But you said it's urgent.

202
00:11:22,633 --> 00:11:23,700
So...

203
00:11:23,833 --> 00:11:24,967
did something happen?

204
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:29,433
Did Dr. Dionela bring any bad
news?

205
00:11:29,567 --> 00:11:31,367
Nothing.

206
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:36,567
I only want you to be here
when Felma wakes up.

207
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:39,500
Why?

208
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:46,567
Felma looked for you earlier
when she woke up.

209
00:12:05,867 --> 00:12:07,000
Dear...

210
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,367
Your dad...

211
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:14,167
Your real dad...

212
00:12:15,433 --> 00:12:17,367
I think I saw him last night.

213
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:24,900
Jojo, was it really you?

214
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:38,667
There are a few effects
expected after the surgery.

215
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:42,567
You may experience motor
coordination issues,

216
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:44,467
especially with
the hands and feet.

217
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:50,033
It's also normal to have
slurred or slow speech.

218
00:12:52,133 --> 00:12:54,833
We will assess her more
once she's wide awake.

219
00:12:57,267 --> 00:13:00,733
Doctor...

220
00:13:00,867 --> 00:13:03,833
my children.

221
00:13:07,733 --> 00:13:10,300
Jeffrey...

222
00:13:13,767 --> 00:13:16,800
Andrea...

223
00:13:19,533 --> 00:13:22,100
Coleen...

224
00:13:24,033 --> 00:13:25,000
Manuel...

225
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:27,833
she remembers your kids.

226
00:13:29,367 --> 00:13:30,733
Thank God.

227
00:13:35,333 --> 00:13:37,400
Noah.

228
00:13:39,067 --> 00:13:40,433
Felma.

229
00:13:43,933 --> 00:13:44,767
I'm here.

230
00:13:48,033 --> 00:13:50,233
Noah.

231
00:13:52,567 --> 00:13:56,067
Thank you...

232
00:13:58,133 --> 00:14:02,467
for not...

233
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:05,600
leaving me.

234
00:14:10,367 --> 00:14:13,200
I owe you...

235
00:14:15,033 --> 00:14:19,800
a lot.

236
00:14:20,967 --> 00:14:22,300
Don't mention it.

237
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:31,033
Felma...

238
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:32,967
by the way.

239
00:14:33,567 --> 00:14:35,333
Manuel's here, too.

240
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:48,733
Felma.

241
00:14:50,367 --> 00:14:52,500
Manuel.

242
00:14:53,500 --> 00:14:54,333
Felma.

243
00:15:03,733 --> 00:15:07,433
Why are you here?

244
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:13,200
What are you doing here?

245
00:15:13,333 --> 00:15:14,600
Felma, Felma.

246
00:15:14,733 --> 00:15:21,067
Leave.

247
00:15:23,467 --> 00:15:24,300
Miss Felma.

248
00:15:24,433 --> 00:15:25,933
Doc.

249
00:15:26,067 --> 00:15:26,933
Miss Felma.

250
00:15:27,067 --> 00:15:28,200
Breathe.

251
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:29,633
Felma.

252
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,833
Felma, calm down.

253
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:40,800
Get out of here!

254
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:47,467
- That's Manuel, Felma.
- You left...

255
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,833
- the kids and me.
- Felma, that's Manuel.

256
00:15:50,133 --> 00:15:54,633
You left me.

257
00:15:54,767 --> 00:15:56,633
- Come on, let's go.
- Please relax.

258
00:15:59,867 --> 00:16:01,267
Felma.

259
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:04,533
Go to your wife!

260
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:16,333
He's a cheater.

261
00:16:16,467 --> 00:16:21,200
Cheater!

262
00:16:22,533 --> 00:16:23,900
He's no longer here.

263
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:27,233
He has left.

264
00:16:28,667 --> 00:16:29,333
Doctor...

265
00:16:30,500 --> 00:16:31,300
what happened?

266
00:16:31,433 --> 00:16:33,833
My wife is mad at me again.

267
00:16:33,967 --> 00:16:36,100
We just made up.

268
00:16:37,633 --> 00:16:39,267
As I mentioned,

269
00:16:39,933 --> 00:16:41,233
the patient
may have memory lapses

270
00:16:41,733 --> 00:16:46,400
or confusion after surgery.

271
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:50,133
The frontal lobe helps with...

272
00:16:51,167 --> 00:16:54,767
memory, focus,
and decision-making.

273
00:16:54,900 --> 00:16:57,567
That's why the patient
is affected temporarily.

274
00:16:58,967 --> 00:17:01,667
Don't worry because the brain
is still healing.

275
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:05,800
We usually see improvements
over a few days or weeks.

276
00:17:07,433 --> 00:17:08,200
Doctor...

277
00:17:09,233 --> 00:17:12,900
what else can we do to help her
memory come back sooner?

278
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:14,267
It would be better

279
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:17,933
to have a calm
and reassuring environment.

280
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:21,633
Talk to her softly,
remind her gently,

281
00:17:21,767 --> 00:17:24,700
and let's avoid
over-stimulation.

282
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:29,333
Doctor, is it okay
for her to see me?

283
00:17:29,467 --> 00:17:31,167
Or will it stress
her out more?

284
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:34,433
Well, if she sees you
and gets triggered again,

285
00:17:34,567 --> 00:17:36,733
you'd better stay away
from her for now.

286
00:17:36,867 --> 00:17:40,433
Anyway, we'll monitor
her progress

287
00:17:40,567 --> 00:17:44,467
and let you know
if there are any updates.

288
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:46,700
What's important
is she's stable

289
00:17:46,833 --> 00:17:50,533
and recovering as expected.

290
00:17:50,700 --> 00:17:52,833
I'll go back
to the patient for now.

291
00:18:06,933 --> 00:18:09,600
Manuel, it's not your fault.

292
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,267
And Felma's not to blame either.

293
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:13,933
As the doctor said,

294
00:18:14,867 --> 00:18:18,433
memory lapses are expected
after brain surgery.

295
00:18:20,300 --> 00:18:22,167
I understand, bro.

296
00:18:23,667 --> 00:18:25,733
I hurt Felma so much.

297
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:28,933
And that's what
stuck in her memory.

298
00:18:31,233 --> 00:18:32,200
Bro,

299
00:18:33,567 --> 00:18:35,733
please take care of her for now.

300
00:18:35,867 --> 00:18:39,233
She's more
comfortable with you.

301
00:18:39,367 --> 00:18:40,500
I'm okay with it.

302
00:18:41,233 --> 00:18:42,500
What if...

303
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:46,000
she still doesn't want
to see you?

304
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:49,900
I admit, bro.

305
00:18:50,033 --> 00:18:51,000
It hurts so much.

306
00:18:52,067 --> 00:18:53,467
It feels so heavy.

307
00:18:55,367 --> 00:18:56,433
But I can handle that

308
00:18:56,567 --> 00:18:59,200
than seeing Felma
struggling and angry.

309
00:19:01,800 --> 00:19:03,833
I'll follow the doctor's advice.

310
00:19:04,967 --> 00:19:07,633
I'll just show up
when she looks for me.

311
00:19:26,567 --> 00:19:29,867
<i>I promised you back then
that if you ever got sick,</i>

312
00:19:30,033 --> 00:19:32,300
<i>I'd be the one
to take care of you.</i>

313
00:19:32,433 --> 00:19:34,633
<i>You're only allowed to get sick
if I'm right by your side.</i>

314
00:19:34,767 --> 00:19:36,500
<i>Because I want to be the one
looking after you.</i>

315
00:19:36,633 --> 00:19:38,500
<i> Just me, no one else.</i>

316
00:19:39,533 --> 00:19:43,033
How can I look after you
when you're shutting me out

317
00:19:43,167 --> 00:19:46,167
because of my past mistake?

318
00:20:08,100 --> 00:20:10,267
Dad, why did you come home?
Did you leave Mom alone?

319
00:20:13,367 --> 00:20:15,933
It's okay.
Your Uncle Noah's there.

320
00:20:16,067 --> 00:20:18,533
He'll look after your mom
for now.

321
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:23,367
Dad, are you sure
you're okay with that?

322
00:20:24,633 --> 00:20:25,567
Dad...

323
00:20:26,133 --> 00:20:30,467
We understand that you and Uncle
Noah are getting along now.

324
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:35,533
It's just unexpected that
you'd leave them alone together.

325
00:20:35,700 --> 00:20:37,767
The truth is,

326
00:20:37,900 --> 00:20:40,400
your mom's memory was affected.

327
00:20:42,333 --> 00:20:44,033
She doesn't want
to see me anymore.

328
00:20:45,533 --> 00:20:46,767
Because of what happened
in Saudi Arabia?

329
00:20:47,833 --> 00:20:48,800
With Hazel?

330
00:20:50,233 --> 00:20:52,033
I can no longer take care
of her.

331
00:20:53,633 --> 00:20:55,467
Noah's lucky.

332
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:59,367
Felma remembers good
memories with him.

333
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:08,067
There. Keep on eating
to regain your strength.

334
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:12,067
Let me do it.

335
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,633
Okay. There.

336
00:21:18,333 --> 00:21:19,967
I can't.

337
00:21:20,100 --> 00:21:23,000
- Do you want more?
- I don't want.

338
00:21:23,133 --> 00:21:25,800
You've barely eaten
anything yet.

339
00:21:25,933 --> 00:21:26,833
Let's do this instead.

340
00:21:27,500 --> 00:21:31,200
If you like to eat more or
you're hungry, just let me know.

341
00:21:32,767 --> 00:21:33,467
Dad...

342
00:21:34,333 --> 00:21:37,333
don't take it to heart
too much.

343
00:21:39,233 --> 00:21:44,767
It's just because
of Mom's surgery.

344
00:21:49,067 --> 00:21:49,967
But dear,

345
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:55,300
it's only fair
that she's blaming me.

346
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:58,533
She never did it before.

347
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:02,667
She couldn't do it in person
since I wasn't around.

348
00:22:03,733 --> 00:22:07,500
Dad, it's already
a closed chapter.

349
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:13,567
But all my mistakes
came back to me.

350
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:15,533
Even when I wasn't there,

351
00:22:17,133 --> 00:22:23,633
I felt how much pain
and suffering I caused you.

352
00:22:26,733 --> 00:22:28,633
So again, kids,

353
00:22:28,767 --> 00:22:30,533
I'm really sorry.

354
00:22:32,900 --> 00:22:33,533
Dad...

355
00:22:34,267 --> 00:22:35,900
we've already forgiven you.

356
00:22:36,033 --> 00:22:37,200
Mom and us.

357
00:22:38,367 --> 00:22:40,367
So don't be discouraged, Dad.

358
00:22:41,033 --> 00:22:44,133
What's happening to Mom right
now is due to her illness.

359
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:47,300
We love you so much, Dad.
Always remember that.

360
00:22:48,733 --> 00:22:50,500
I love you so much, too.

361
00:22:53,667 --> 00:22:56,333
Let me get a hug
from my dearest ones.

362
00:23:06,533 --> 00:23:10,867
What if it takes a while
before Mom's memories come back?

363
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:13,933
Will she stay sweet to
Uncle Noah for a long time?

364
00:23:14,067 --> 00:23:16,667
I'll patiently wait
for that day to come.

365
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:19,433
We need the help
of other therapists.

366
00:23:19,567 --> 00:23:22,633
You mean, she will be
able to function normally again?

367
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:26,867
Yes. Miss Felma, I'd like you
to meet your physical therapist.

368
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,300
Joselito Cañares.

369
00:23:28,433 --> 00:23:29,733
Good day, Miss Felma.

370
00:23:29,867 --> 00:23:32,167
We'll start with
simple exercises.

371
00:23:32,300 --> 00:23:33,733
Sitting up, standing...

372
00:23:33,867 --> 00:23:38,733
This way, we can help our body
and brain coordinate again.

373
00:23:38,867 --> 00:23:39,733
Felma.
